  "prompt": "Can I deactivate my Roku device?",
  "response": "Yes, you can deactivate your Roku device if you no longer wish to use it or want to unlink it from your Roku account. Here\u2019s how you can do it:\n\n1. **Factory Reset the Device**: This will remove all data and unlink the device from your account.\n    - Go to the home screen and select \"Settings\".\n    - Select \"System\".\n    - Select \"Advanced system settings\".\n    - Select \"Factory reset\".\n    - Follow the prompts to complete the reset.\n\n2. **Unlink from Roku Account**:\n   - Visit the Roku website and log into your account.\n   - Go to \"My Account\".\n   - Scroll down to \"My linked devices\".\n   - Find the device you want to deactivate and click \"Unlink\".\n\nAfter following these steps, your Roku device will be deactivated and unlinked from your account. If you want to use it again in the future, you will need to perform the setup process again.",
